[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    502[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173m"OOD severity bands are policy, not implementation. The chapter-wide defaults (suppress at >= 0.85, warn at >= 0.50, present normally below) are starting points; per-pair overrides are available in the treatment-catalog when clinically warranted (e.g., a pair with a very narrow training-cohort distribution may need a tighter suppress threshold). Suppression is the chapter's most defensive clinical-safety primitive: a numeric estimate that the model itself does not believe is reliable should not be presented to a clinician at the point of care, even with a caveat. The validator (Finding S3) and the OOD bands (this finding) are co-specified; changes to one require corresponding changes to the other."[38;2;180;142;173m*[K
