[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     932[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Same colloquial-versus-corporate-marketing tension as 4.6 V3 and 4.7 V3. Both uses are the "leverage point" sense, not the "leverage AWS services" verb. Acceptable in context. If the editor's pass tightens marketing-adjacent terminology generally, these are the candidates.[K
